overherd README

--INTRO--

overheard is a java-based project for visually displaying online discussion
boards. It relies heavily on perfuse (http://prefuse.org) to build interactive
visualizations. Overherd is distributed under the Apache 2.0 license with the 
following boilerplate message:

   Copyright 2010 Regents of the University of Michigan

   Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");
   you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.
   You may obtain a copy of the License at

       http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

   Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software
   distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,
   WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.
   See the License for the specific language governing permissions and
   limitations under the License.

-- REQUIREMENTS --

To compile and run Overherd, you'll need a copy of the Java Development Kit (JDK)
version 1.6 or greater. You can get the most recent version of the JDK from
http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html

The build instructions below assume you use the NetBeans IDE.

Overherd requires the following libraries:
core.jar
jcommon-1.0.16.jar
jfreechart-1.0.13.jar
lingpipe-3.9.1.jar
prefuse.jar

All libraries are included in the /jars folder.

-- BUILDING IN NETBEANS 6.9.1 ON A MAC --

Before opening NetBeans, make sure you have the most recent version of Overherd
from the git repository. OVERHERD_PATH means the absolute path of where ever you
keep your working copy of the Overherd project.

1. Open NetBeans
2. Select "New Project" from File menu
3. Select "Java Project with Existing Sources" and click Next>
4. Give the project a name, usually Overherd and select the folder where you keep
your working copy as the Project Folder.
5. Leave build.xml as the Build Script Name
6. Choose Next>
7. Choose OVERHERD_PATH/app/src as the Source Package Folder and click Next>
8. Leave the Includes and Excludes as-is and click Finish
9. Right click on "Overherd" in the Projects pane
10. Choose Properties
11. Choose Libraries
12. Click "Add JAR/Folder"
13. Add each .jar file from OVERHERD_PATH/jars individually
14. Click OK
15. Clean and Build the project

Following those steps will create a local NetBeans project and produce a runnable
Overherd.jar in the OVERHERD_PATH/dist folder.

-- RUNNING --
